# sequences_smoke.numos — open the Sequences app, screenshot, and ASSERT it is active.
#
# Phase 7A smoke test. SequencesApp is LVGL-native and emulator-safe: it pulls only
# lvgl + ui::StatusBar + input/KeyCodes + KeyboardManager + a self-contained
# sscanf-based recompute() (no Giac/CAS, no LittleFS/Preferences, no heap_caps/PSRAM,
# no sensors/WiFi; SequencesApp.cpp:25-28,323-367). This script opens it through the
# emulator-only `open_app` command (added in Phase 5A: it calls the SAME NativeHal
# launchApp() the launcher uses — id 7, the Sequences card id — so it is deterministic
# and does not depend on fragile grid navigation), captures a screenshot, and asserts
# the active app is "Sequences".
#
# The app opens on its "Define" tab showing the static default expressions
# u(n)=2*n+1 and v(n)=n^2 (SequencesApp.cpp:68-69,100). SequencesApp has NO update()
# method and no cursor/caret blink, so as with every emulator screen the only volatile
# region across runs is the StatusBar clock (HH:MM). This phase makes NO golden claim;
# the screenshot is a CANDIDATE for human review only (a clock mask is added by the
# human at promotion time, rect 4,6,37,13).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash (~frame 125) is done; we are in the launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Sequences screen load + 200ms fade settles after open_app.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/sequences_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/sequences_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "sequences_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Sequences (emulator launchApp id 7 — same id as the launcher's Sequences card).
open_app Sequences
wait 60

# Screenshot FIRST: the deferred capture happens on this frame, before the assert
# runs on a later frame, so the artifact is produced even if the assertion fails.
screenshot out/sequences_smoke.ppm
log "sequences_smoke: screenshot captured"

assert_app Sequences
log "sequences_smoke: assertion passed (Sequences active)"
